BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:nT_6tuB06CjSY6rCMyeA8
SUMMARY:Capitol Hill & First Hill Business Safety Summit
DTSTAMP:20260402T030258Z
DTSTART:20260406T220000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description You are invited to join fellow Capitol Hill and Fir
	st Hill businesses for a Safety Summit at the Silver Cloud Hotel \\(1100 B
	roadway\\) on Mon\, Apr 6 from 3:00 to 5:00 p.m. This gathering is designe
	d specifically for businesses operating at the street level. This is a gre
	at opportunity to meet the new East Precinct Captain\, hear about helpful 
	programs from the City\, and connect with neighboring businesses facing ma
	ny of the same challenges. Our goal is to work together to support and str
	engthen what makes the business districts of Capitol Hill and First Hill s
	o unique and special. This event is brought to you by the 15th Avenue Busi
	ness Improvement Area\, Broadway Business Improvement Area\, First Hill Im
	provement Association\, and GSBA: Capitol Hill\, with additional support f
	rom 4N & Associates and Silver Cloud Hotel. Meet Our New East Precinct Cap
	tain Captain James Britt\, SPD  Community Assisted Response & Engagement \
	\(CARE\\) Chief Amy Barden\, CARE Learn About Community Assisted Response 
	& Engagement \\(CARE\\) Crime Prevention Through Environmental Design \\(C
	PTED\\) Back to Business Program: Storefront Repair Fund and Storefront Se
	curity Fund Share Bring your safety challenges\, concerns and questions Pr
	ogram 3pm Doors open 3:30pm Speaking program starts followed by social Ple
	ase RSVP  Space is limited. Free Parking! Light food provided. Please brin
	g cash for no host bar.  Pre-event Survey Help shape the conversation at t
	he Safety Summit by sharing any safety challenges\, concerns\, or question
	s you would like addressed. Please submit responses by Friday\, April 3 so
	 we can share common themes with presenters in advance. If you cannot atte
	nd\, we still welcome your input and will share an event recap afterward.\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/capitol-hill-first-hill-b
	usiness-safety-summit/18425343/2026-04-06T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community 
	& Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/capitol-hill-first-hill-b
	usiness-safety-summit/18425343/2026-04-06T00
LOCATION:Stoup Brewing\, 1158 Broadway\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Qe1dS1_0li-iQN3lDm4mp
SUMMARY:Building a More Welcoming Washington: Seattle's FIFA World Cup Incl
	usion Training
DTSTAMP:20260402T030258Z
DTSTART:20260406T220000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description Inclusion Training Initiative: Building a More Welc
	oming Washington As Washington prepares to welcome the world for FIFA Worl
	d Cup 2026\, local businesses will be on the front lines of hospitality-se
	rving visitors\, supporting staff\, and representing the values of our reg
	ion every day. GSBA is partnering with SeattleFWC26 to offer Inclusion Tra
	ining workshops designed to help small businesses and organizations feel p
	repared\, confident\, and welcoming. These sessions provide practical\, re
	al-world guidance on allyship\, gender inclusion\, and LGBTQ\\+ cultural c
	ompetency\, with a focus on everyday customer and workplace interactions. 
	About the Inclusion Training Initiative As part of SeattleFWC26's commitme
	nt to ensuring every fan\, visitor\, and resident feels welcome\, the Incl
	usion Training Initiative-delivered in partnership with GSBA-equips local 
	businesses and organizations with tools to create authentically inclusive 
	environments for LGBTQ\\+ customers\, employees\, and communities.  About 
	River Teslar River \\(she/her\\) is a trans woman and nonprofit profession
	al with four years of experience at GSBA developing and facilitating LGBTQ
	\\+ Inclusion Trainings through a social justice- and trauma-informed lens
	. Drawing from lived experience and community-based work\, she creates lea
	rning spaces grounded in empathy\, curiosity\, and practical application\,
	 where participants feel supported engaging at any level.    Key Activitie
	s ⚽ Four Inclusion Workshops: Hosted by GSBA and tailored for small busine
	sses\, nonprofits\, and frontline teams. ⚽ Interactive Learning: Sessions 
	focus on allyship\, gender inclusion\, and LGBTQ\\+ cultural competency in
	 the workplace\, with real-world scenarios and discussion. ⚽ Accessible Pa
	rticipation: Two in-person workshops hosted at GSBA's Capitol Hill office 
	\\(or other community venues\\) and two virtual workshops open to particip
	ants statewide. ⚽ Practical Tools: Participants receive actionable guidanc
	e and resources to help strengthen inclusive policies\, communications\, a
	nd customer experiences. Outcomes & Benefits ⚽ More Inclusive Businesses: 
	Participating organizations gain the knowledge to create spaces that welco
	me all genders\, identities\, and relationships. ⚽ Community Visibility: S
	trengthens Washington's reputation as a leader in inclusive tourism and co
	mmunity hospitality ahead of FIFA World Cup 2026. ⚽ Economic Impact: Inclu
	sive environments encourage repeat visitation\, word-of-mouth referrals\, 
	and stronger customer loyalty. ⚽ Sustained Legacy: Builds long-term capaci
	ty for inclusion that extends beyond the tournament\, leaving a lasting ma
	rk on Washington's business and tourism ecosystem. Workshop Schedule Virtu
	al Workshops ⚽ Thursday\, January 15 - 10:00 AM ⚽ Wednesday\, March 4 - 3:
	00 PM In-Person Workshops ⚽ Monday\, February 9 - 10:00 AM ⚽ Monday\, Apri
	l 6 - 3:00 PM Learn more about the initiative: SeattleFWC26 Inclusion Trai
	ning Initiative\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/building-
	a-more-welcoming-washington-seattle-s-fifa-world-cup-inclusion-training/18
	234881/2026-04-06T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/building-a-more-welcoming
	-washington-seattle-s-fifa-world-cup-inclusion-training/18234881/2026-04-0
	6T00
LOCATION:GSBA- Washington State&'s LGBTQ+ Chamber of Commerce\, 400 E Pine 
	St Ste 322\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
