	 Scavenger Hunt Starting April 10\, follow the clues\, find hidden dragon 
	eggs throughout the city\, and log your discoveries for a chance to win am
	azing dragon treasure! 2️⃣ Student Poster Contest K–12 students are invited 
	to design the official poster for the 7th Annual Dragon’s Landing Event. W
	inners will have their artwork featured at the event\, in the student art 
	show\, and online! Submissions due March 6 3️⃣ Window Decorating Contest for
	 Businesses Local businesses are invited to decorate their windows in drag
	on-inspired creativity! Show off your storefront\, engage the community\, 
	and add to the festive magic of downtown Renton. ✨ Event Day – Sunday\, Ap
	ril 12\, 2026 Enjoy captivating performances\, creative crafts\, and fun f
	or all ages as we come together to celebrate our rooftop dragon! Sign up f
	or treasure hunt updates here: https://forms.gle/Tt9g8KUmmBPthmgV6 More in
	formation available at Rentonwa.gov/dragonslanding \\(check back for updat
	es!\\) Step into a world of enchantment and let your imagination soar!\n\n
	https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/dragon-s-landing-celebration
	-and-treasure-hunt/18252299/2026-04-12T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & C
	ivic
