BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:VtYVfqFpFTi_OfJoM0f0y
SUMMARY:Write a Feature Film
DTSTAMP:20260402T030259Z
DTSTART:20260415T013000Z
DESCRIPTION:Class Overview\n\nDo you want to write a screenplay for a featu
	re film\, but don’t know where to start? Perhaps you’re a beginner curious
	 about the mechanics of screenplays\, or a longtime writer feeling a bit s
	tuck\, or a director who would enjoy a new perspective. In this class\, ga
	in the skills to turn your ideas into a solid screenplay for a feature fil
	m.\n\nGain the tools and building blocks to help guide each part of the wr
	iting process for a feature-length screenplay. Learn how to be successful 
	with each step\, from idea generation\, to writing and revising\, and espe
	cially outlining and structuring your film.\n\nEach 90-minute class will i
	nclude one or more short in-class exercises\, from brainstorming to writin
	g and revising scenes. In the sixth and final class\, you will have an opp
	ortunity to read an excerpt of your script or present a detailed synopsis 
	to classmates. You’ll be encouraged to work between classes.\n\nWe’ll look
	 at ways to organize your ideas into an outline that can advance progressi
	vely closer to a feature film\, discussing diverse and alternative approac
	hes in your structure that might help your script connect with audiences w
	ithout using clichés. Explore how three-dimensional characters drive plot 
	and how setting\, staging\, and dialogue can be used to tell your story in
	 an energetic\, immersive way. We’ll discuss the differences between writi
	ng a screenplay you plan to direct yourself versus one you’re writing for 
	someone else. \n\nThere will be handouts and/or reading suggestions offere
	d in class. We’ll look at excerpts from books such as Aristotle’s Poetics 
	and Susan Sontag’s Against Interpretation\, as well as film clips and inte
	rviews with a diverse array of famous filmmakers across time and space.\n\
	nGet support and guidance on how to find inspiration for your own personal
	 artistic expression and the drive to finish your project. Explore the man
	y joys that can be found in this unique\, creative\, and multifaceted art 
	form.\n\nLearning Objectives\n\nBrainstorm and organize ideas for a screen
	play\n\nApproach structure in a flexible way that allows for different typ
	es of films\n\nCreate three-dimensional characters that form the basis of 
	a story\n\nHow form can be progressive and new\, just like content\n\nFind
	 your voice and learn to write comfortably and confidently as yourself\n\n
	Who Might Enjoy This Class?\n\nWriters interested in exploring how they mi
	ght approach a screenplay\n\nAnyone who wants to develop their voice as a 
	screenwriter and filmmaker\n\nPeople who have begun a feature-length scree
	nplay and would like the support to continue\n\nArtists drawn to other par
	ts of the filmmaking process who would like to explore the writing side\n\
	nAnyone interested in how films are structured and what screenplays are ma
	de of\n\nFilmmakers who want to create an unconventional piece without sac
	rificing character and structure\n\nNo experience is needed\; everyone is 
	welcome!\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/write-a-feature-
	film/18345429/2026-04-14T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Education
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/write-a-feature-film/1834
	5429/2026-04-14T00
LOCATION:Seattle Central College Continuing Education\, 1701 Broadway\, Sea
	ttle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gkmlclpKFkcwOIBuDDKPD
SUMMARY:Chuckle Bucket Tuesday @ Club Comedy Seattle (Open Mic)
DTSTAMP:20260402T030259Z
DTSTART:20260415T020000Z
DESCRIPTION:Club Comedy Seattle hosts Chuckle Bucket Tuesday each week. The
	 luck of the bucket rules the night. Comics drop their name in and hope to
	 be drawn for one of the spots on the list to tell jokes. It's fun\, fast-
	paced and will keep you laughing hard on your Tuesday night.\n\nDoor 7:00P
	M/Show 7:30PM\n\nAdmission: $7 \\+ $0.35 City Of Seattle Admission Tax\n\n
	21\\+ With Valid ID REQUIRED for entry. NO REFUNDS.\n\nFYI: If you have a 
	large party it's easier for us to seat you all together if you purchase al
	l the tickets under one name.\n\n.\n\nClub Comedy Seattle FAQ\n\nIs there 
	an age/ID requirement?\n\nYes. We are strictly 21\\+ and valid physical ID
	 is REQUIRED For Entry\n\nIs Seating First Come/First Served?\n\nYes. The 
	room is all two top tables and we seat guests in the order in which they a
	rrive.\n\nCan I reserve a table for a group?\n\nWe do not take reservation
	s for tables\, but groups can arrive early to secure seating together.\n\n
	Are tickets available at the door if an event is sold out online?\n\nIf an
	 event is sold out online there are no tickets available at the door.\n\nW
	hat are the club’s hours of operation?\n\nThe club is open Tuesday to Sund
	ay. Doors open a half hour before each show.\n\nWhat is the Parking like?\
	n\nGenerally there is street parking available in the blocks surrounding t
	he club. There are also affordable parking lots on 16th Ave E right around
	 the block from the club along with other easy options in the neighborhood
	\n\nIs there a dress code?\n\nThere is no formal dress code\, but we recom
	mend smart casual attire.\n\nCan I bring food or drinks?\n\nOutside food a
	nd drinks are not allowed. We have a full bar and a menu available for you
	r enjoyment.\n\nWhat if I can't make it and need to cancel my ticket?\n\nA
	ll ticket sales are final. However\, if you can’t make it\, please contact
	 us through Eventbrite in advance\, and we’ll do our best to accommodate y
	ou.\n\nWill there be an opener for the headliner?\n\nYes\, headliner shows
	 feature a lineup of comedians\, including a host\, an opener\, and the he
	adliner.\n\nWill the comics talk to me like I see in online videos all the
	 time?\n\nMost likely they won't. Crowd work videos are popular for postin
	g online\, but crowd work doesn't generally happen at the online frequency
	 in live comedy show situations. Some comics do engage the crowd as part o
	f their regular set and it's generally always fun and more about making fu
	n of themselves than making fun of the crowd.\n\nHow can I get on the Chea
	p Laughs Open Mic On Wednesdays?\n\nSubmissions for spots on the Wednesday
	 Cheap Laughs Open Mic are accepted only on the Tuesday before between 12:
	00AM and 11:59PM via email at openmic@clubcomedyseattle.com\n\nDo you offe
	r group discounts?\n\nYes\, we offer discounts for groups of ten or more. 
	Please contact us for more details.\n\nCan I meet the comedians after the 
	show?\n\nMeet-and-greet opportunities vary by event. Please ask staff for 
	details after the show.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/c
	huckle-bucket-tuesday-club-comedy-seattle-open-mic/18474121/2026-04-14T00\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/chuckle-bucket-tuesday-cl
	ub-comedy-seattle-open-mic/18474121/2026-04-14T00
LOCATION:Club Comedy Seattle\, 328 15th Ave E\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
