BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Dh5jrBvHsVLLz0hrb6CUm
SUMMARY:Wednesday Cheap Laughs Open Mic @ Club Comedy Seattle
DTSTAMP:20260402T030300Z
DTSTART:20260416T020000Z
DESCRIPTION:Club Comedy Seattle hosts our Weekly Stand-Up Comedy Open Mic E
	very Wednesday. Door 7:30PM/Show 8:00PM. Come see how the jokes are made.\
	n\nAdmission for the Open Mic is just $7 \\+ $0.35 City Of Seattle Admissi
	on Tax\n\n21\\+ With Valid ID REQUIRED for entry. NO REFUNDS.\n\nClub Come
	dy Seattle FAQ\n\nIs there an age/ID requirement?\n\nYes. We are strictly 
	21\\+ and valid physical ID is REQUIRED For Entry\n\nIs Seating First Come
	/First Served?\n\nYes. The room is all two top tables and we seat guests i
	n the order in which they arrive.\n\nCan I reserve a table for a group?\n\
	nWe do not take reservations for tables\, but groups can arrive early to s
	ecure seating together.\n\nAre tickets available at the door if an event i
	s sold out online?\n\nIf an event is sold out online there are no tickets 
	available at the door.\n\nWhat are the club’s hours of operation?\n\nThe c
	lub is open Tuesday to Sunday. Doors open a half hour before each show.\n\
	nWhat is the Parking like?\n\nGenerally there is street parking available 
	in the blocks surrounding the club. There are also affordable parking lots
	 on 16th Ave E right around the block from the club along with other easy 
	options in the neighborhood\n\nIs there a dress code?\n\nThere is no forma
	l dress code\, but we recommend smart casual attire.\n\nCan I bring food o
	r drinks?\n\nOutside food and drinks are not allowed. We have a full bar a
	nd a menu available for your enjoyment.\n\nWhat if I can't make it and nee
	d to cancel my ticket?\n\nAll ticket sales are final. However\, if you can
	’t make it\, please contact us through Eventbrite in advance\, and we’ll d
	o our best to accommodate you.\n\nWill there be an opener for the headline
	r?\n\nYes\, headliner shows feature a lineup of comedians\, including a ho
	st\, an opener\, and the headliner.\n\nWill the comics talk to me like I s
	ee in online videos all the time?\n\nMost likely they won't. Crowd work vi
	deos are popular for posting online\, but crowd work doesn't generally hap
	pen at the online frequency in live comedy show situations. Some comics do
	 engage the crowd as part of their regular set and it's generally always f
	un and more about making fun of themselves than making fun of the crowd.\n
	\nHow can I get on the Cheap Laughs Open Mic On Wednesdays?\n\nSubmissions
	 for spots on the Wednesday Cheap Laughs Open Mic are accepted only on the
	 Tuesday before between 12:00AM and 11:59PM via email at openmic@clubcomed
	yseattle.com\n\nDo you offer group discounts?\n\nYes\, we offer discounts 
	for groups of ten or more. Please contact us for more details.\n\nCan I me
	et the comedians after the show?\n\nMeet-and-greet opportunities vary by e
	vent. Please ask staff for details after the show.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6am
	city.com/events/#/details/wednesday-cheap-laughs-open-mic-club-comedy-seat
	tle/18473857/2026-04-15T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/wednesday-cheap-laughs-op
	en-mic-club-comedy-seattle/18473857/2026-04-15T00
LOCATION:Club Comedy Seattle\, 328 15th Ave E\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
